<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057110-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 7 and b = 4. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.1</li><li>60.3</li><li>29.7</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{4}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={49}+{16}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={65}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{65}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.0622577482985}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.1}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{7}}{{4}}\right)}}}\approx{60.255118703058}\approx{60.3}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{60.255118703058}^{\circ}\approx{29.744881296942}\approx{29.7}</m>.</p>

</solution>
